Title: ELECTRIC! The Mid-drive eBike that Shreds! CyberBike eMountain Bikes!
text: Introducing the New 2022 Cyberbike Electric Mountain Bikes   Riders agree: Nothing comes close to Cyberbike's combination of performance, value, style, and quality.  See the Cyberbike Mullet Pro in action HERE! (and here, by popular demand, is last year's intro featuring Division 1 Collegiate Mountain Racer Corey Jackson on the first edition Cyberbike) Order online for fast delivery at www.Cyberbike.com All 2022 Cyberbikes are in stock and ready to shred, Order yours before they're sold out!  More mid-drive power than ever Awesome new color graphic display Easier to ride, lower standover frame, the lowest of any mid-drive eMTB New, structurally superior, mountain ready rear suspension linkage The best brakes in the business, even Quad-piston brakes on some models! Massive brake rotors up to 220mm 34mm gold tube forks on some models up to 140mm travel Wider range of models  A proper e-Mountain bike needs to be mid-drive and have full suspension, it's as simple as that. Until now, if you wanted an electric mountain bike to tackle rugged trails, your choices have been heavy, low-quality, fat tire, hub-motor beach bikes, or legacy brands charging $4000 or more for low-power eBikes without full suspension.   Whether your knees are tired or you just want to shred, there is simply no better choice for performance and value than Cyberbike. An American company with great customer support: Cyberbike, USA. The mountains are calling. Will you answer?  Cyberbike eBikes come all with the quietest and most powerful motor in its class, with a long range (65 miles and more) battery, and powerful e-spec hydraulic disk brakes that will be there when you need them. A lightweight package with 500 watts of power, top-of-the-line battery range, and quality components, all for the price of an inexpensive yet stellar bike! You'll get so much more than other eBikes with the CyberBike, it's the real e-MTB experience for the adventurous rider. Performance, specs, and quality components throughout, and the best warranty in the industry, from an American company with experienced American mechanics on call for all your tech support needs.  54 volt/500 watt climbing power with 13Amp hour Li-Ion battery and only 52 lbs means you'll get power and tons of battery range. Now with available throttle! Now from only $2495 Note: Owning and riding comes with risks. Wear proper protection, properly maintain and check your bike, and ride within your limits. By purchasing our products you agree to take full responsibility for the ownership of your bike, including the above and all other reasonable precautions for yourself or anyone you allow to ride your bike.

Title: 2009 Yamaha Vino 125 cc scooter
text: 2009 Yamaha Vino 125 cc scooter. $1250.00  The Vino is one of my favorite scooters. We have been servicing many of them for many years and they are proven quality right along side the Vespas and Honda scooters.   Fun, practical, reliable, simple and 72.5 mpg!  This was a trade in for a musician that was ready for a biger bike.  In March 2022 we replaced the front tire, changed the oil and filter and did a full inspection.  Yamaha claims it will do 55 miles per hour. I got it up to 50 on our little side street.  Fuelly.com shows these getting an average of 72.5 miles per gallon. Lots of locking storage under the seat. Mechanically it is very nice. It has a lot of scratches as seen in the pictures but no broken plastic  and no problems. This is a great value for around town or to put on the back of your RV for camping trips. You might even want to add a rear trunk or a simple basket on the rear.    Watch the video on my website and discover more about us. Please copy and paste this link into your browser:  https://www.samscycle.net/2009-yamaha-vino-125-72-mpg-dollar1250_00    Please be careful when shopping for scooters. If it is a brand name that sounds familiar then  it is worth considering. Most of the China made scooters look new and shinny but are not quality and parts are hard to find. We do not service most China made bikes.  We do service everything we sell.     Thanks for taking the time to share in the fun, pride and adventure we find on and off road.  I have been right here in this same location since 1976 and full time with employees since 1982.  We service everything we sell. Title: 2008 Suzuki VL800 Boulevard C50 low miles
text: Super nice mid sized bike that gets over 48 miles per gallon!   It is big enough for cross country adventures and small enough for around town.  This is a very practical way to commute in style while saving on gas and insurance.  Why buy new and take that huge depreciation on day one?  Why buy new and pay the higher insurance, taxes and anual registration renewals?  This bike has never been dropped. It is beautiful but does have some minor scratches as pointed out in the pictures and the rear fender has a small crack under the tail light.  This is a second owner bike. It comes as pictured with the nice factory Suzuki Boulevard saddle bags,  tall windshield, engine guasrds, floor boards, chrome rack, accessory LED safety lights on the front  forks and flashing red around the lisence plate. Also somes with the owners manual.  This is about as nice of a mix of practicality and cool style that you will find.  Very low miles, fully serviced, needs nothing, fantastic gas mileage, very comfortable and classy looking. The tires are in good condition. We have been servicing this bike at our shop for a few years. We did a full inspection, cleaned the air filter and replaced the  battery in February. My customers have used many different competitively priced door to door shipping services. No crating ever needed.  A simple Google search for "motorcycle shipping" will bring up lots of options. Title: 2010 Customized Rpod 174 - ON CONSIGNMENT
text: If you are interested in seeing this great travel trailer, please read consignment notes at the bottom of this posting Selling my great Rpod174 because I bought a larger travel trailer.  It comes fully equipped and has lots of extras.  It has low mileage usage.  The original owner used it for weekend motorcycle trips.  He thought that he only put on 2500-3000 miles.   I have had it about 3 years and pulled it 5000 miles.  Recently replaced all of the locks on this great RV  Custom hitch (worth $1900) with 60" x 20" lockable tool box. That tool box alone is worth $500  Extended length which allows storage of a couple of bikes or small scooter.  I have added both a second battery and propane tank.  Electric hitch post.  Note that this model has wheels outside the bottom of the trailer which makes for much greater stability. Plus the tires are off road capable for those who want to do serious boondocking. It comes with a sway.  I'm also including a 2400 watt generator.(worth $350)  It can't power everything at once but will do a great job if you're careful how much electricity you need while cooking, running the furnace, etc.   I also added two Harbor freight scissor jacks for front stability because the ones included by Forrest River were very insufficient.   Inside, I placed a queen sized futon mattress (w/ springs).  One of the pieces supporting the mattress is designed to be the nook table but the legs are removed.   The detached legs are included.  I also added a small floor freezer (worth $150) so I could enlarge the refrigerator for just cooling items.  Comes with a small remotely operated TV on a mount that allows the TV to be viewed on the couch or bed.  Comes standard with furnace, A/C, fan in the bathroom, sink, propane stove, electric/propane water heater, and a small couch that converts to a kids bed. Decent amount of cabinets but it is a small trailer after all.  The sink faucet has a broken handle but I have purchased a better one that need to be installed.   I'm including sewer hoses, tire stops, and fresh water hose.  Hitch ball is 2"  The standard weight of an Rpod174 is 2300 pounds.  With the custom hitch and second propane tank/battery it will have a dry weight of around 3080 pounds. (certified scale weight)   Add to that the water and cargo you plan to carry in both the trailer and your tow vehicle and make sure it is capable of pulling that weight. (think 3800+) I used a straight 6 Trailblazer LS and it travelled fine, although a bit slow going up long steep hills.  Small SUV's cannot pull this unit safely.  The overall length is 23 feet.   I had Mario's RV Repair check it all out and everything is working.  They did replace the cables from the propane tanks to the splitter and a lose wire on the refrigerator.  ($350 charge) This unit is ready to roll.   The license plate and title are both from Colorado since I live in Denver.  Title is clear. No trades!  Low ballers will be ignored!!   I strongly prefer communication by email or text (I have hearing issues) so sent me a phone number that is textable.  It's currently in storage in N Palm Springs.  I'm in no hurry to sell it. Once again low ballers will be ignored.  Consignment notes:  To view this trailer you must provide me with a phone number to have a short conversation about the consignment process.  Basically you will be working with a business owner in downtown DHS as well as the storage facility where it's located, also in DHS.  Viewing hours are slightly limited due to the limited access to the storage facility.  The buyer will need to bring part cash (for the consignee) and a cashier check which will be mailed to my bank. Thanks for considering my great Rpod

Here is a glimpse at just the top ten uses of utility trailers:  1.Automobiles: From time to time it becomes necessary to haul an inoperable car or truck. Tow trucks are expensive, especially if the distance is great. A utility trailer is a great way to haul vehicles and a good investment if you need to do so regularly.  2.Boats: If you have a boat, you will need a utility trailer to get it to and from the water.  3.Lawn Care Equipment: If you live in a rural area, you may find that you need to haul your mowing equipment from one piece of your property to another. Packing equipment and loading it into a pickup truck bed can get old very quickly. A utility trailer will allow you to drive your equipment right up onto the trailer without the aid of ramps or two strong men.  4.Furniture: Moving furniture is a breeze with a utility trailer. Furniture dollies roll right up onto the trailer and you can haul more than you can with a pickup.  5.Building Supplies: Do you have projects that need to be done around the house? Pick up your own building supplies and save on delivery fees.  6.Bikes, Motorcycles, and ATVs: Recreational vehicles are best hauled on a utility trailer.  7.Livestock: An enclosed utility trailer is most often used to haul livestock.  8.Auction and Flea Markets: If you frequent auctions and flea markets, you will need the hauling capability to bring home your inexpensive and rare finds.  9.Appliances: Utility trailers are ideal for hauling appliances.  10.Debris and Trash: Loading trash in and out of your pickup bed can be cumbersome and clean up can be messy, but it would be worse to have to haul trash in your SUV. Clean up after a big job is a lot easier with a utility trailer.  As you can see, there are many reasons why an investment in a utility trailer is a smart move. Title: 2001 Suzuki DR650 with 790 big bore kit and tons of extras
text: IF THE AD IS UP, THE BIKE IS STILL AVAILABLE  2001 DR650 with ~24,400 miles ‚Ä¢ Procycle 790 big bore kit with Carillo Piston (~2k miles on top end / puts out 50+ hp and torque) ‚Ä¢ TM40 pumper carb ‚Ä¢ Acerbis 5.3 gallon fuel tank ‚Ä¢ Fastway adventure pegs ‚Ä¢ Firepower lithium battery ‚Ä¢ JNS foot peg lowering kit ‚Ä¢ Ricor Intiminator front forks and recent 5w fork service (spare front forks included) ‚Ä¢ Eibach spring on rear shock (spare original also included) ‚Ä¢ Seat concepts comfort seat ‚Ä¢ LED headlight and tail lights ‚Ä¢ USB charger with voltmeter ‚Ä¢ Twinair air filter ‚Ä¢ Acerbis skid plate ‚Ä¢ Enduro engineering handguards ‚Ä¢ Motoz Tractionator RallZ rear tire (400 miles on it) ‚Ä¢ Motoz Tractionator IT front (60% left) ‚Ä¢ New front and rear sprockets ‚Ä¢ New rear brake pads (still in package) ‚Ä¢ Protaper bars and grips ‚Ä¢ Fresh oil change with K+N filter, Motul oil ‚Ä¢ RMZ front fender (original included) ‚Ä¢ Warp 9 chain guide  The bike is very comfortable for someone of average size (5'8" - 6'0") for extended periods of time. The 790 kit really woke up the bottom end and made it way more responsive. Power from about 2k up depending on gear. Having ridden my wife's DR back to back with mine, the difference is immediately apparent. The DR is a legend around RTW (round the world) travellers due to its reliability and ease of finding parts. The #1 complaint is typically the neutral safety switch in the motor (which has been fixed on this one). It is easy to find examples of these bikes goin 80k miles or more. The extended range tank nets around 225 miles until empty, giving the bike very good range. Riding through Death Valley a few weeks back, fuel range was of no concern.   Tons of spare parts, spare rear wheel, spare front forks, spare rear shock and other parts also included. We bought a parts bike and stripped it of useful parts. Not interested in trades, not interested in discussing price over the phone. Price is negotiable within reason. Text message is preferred. Bought a new bike and can't ride two at the same time.

text: Low miles, garage kept and well maintained.. 2015 Ducati Multistrada 1200s touring Comes with folding motorcycle trailer,trunk, side panniers, tank bag, helmet with sena 20s intercom, Bike has Shorai lithium battery upgrade with maintainer, Custome Corbin heated seat, riding gear and cooling vest/system and many custom parts. Have ridden bike all around Utah and southern California in 110+ temp with no problem. With cooling system and heated seats and grips, this is truly a 4 season bike.   Thanks to the new riding mode technology, the Multistrada 1200 could be considered as four bikes in one, being designed to respond to multiple uses. Its advanced electronics allowed the rider to select a series of specific parameters at the touch of a button, which adapted this bike to four different situations: from touring to off-road, from sporty riding to city cruising.

With our comprehensive selection of motorcycles, we will find the right bike for any rider level and discipline from cruisers, standard and naked motorcycles, sport touring, adventure, dual sport to full blown super-sport bikes.  Whether it‚Äôs the famous Kawasaki Ninja 300, Ninja 400, Ninja 650, Z650, Honda CBR300R, CB300F, CBR500R, Yamaha R3, FZ6R, the FZ07 or any of the top of the line super sport bikes such as the Honda CBR600RR, Kawasaki Ninja ZX6R, Suzuki GSXR 600, GSXR 750, or Yamaha R6. If you‚Äôre into bigger bikes, we also carry the Yamaha R1, FZ09, FZ10, Suzuki GSXR 1000, Hayabusa GSX1300R, Kawasaki ZX10R, ZX14R, Ninja 1000, the Z1000, and the incredible BMW S1000RR.
